      p
      | While Celebrate Together generally provides a lot of leeway in what content is acceptable, here are some guidelines for content that is not. Please keep in mind the spirit in which these were written, and know that looking for loopholes is a waste of time.
      h5(style='margin-top:10px;') Content is prohibited if it
      ul
        li Is illegal
        li Is involuntary pornography
        li Is sexual or suggestive content involving minors
        li Encourages or incites violence
        li Threatens, harasses, or bullies or encourages others to do so
        li Is personal and confidential information
        li Impersonates someone in a misleading or deceptive manner
        li
          | Uses Celebrate Together to solicit or facilitate any transaction or gift involving certain goods and services
        li Is spam
      br
      h5 Prohibited behavior
      | In addition to not submitting unwelcome content, the following behaviors are prohibited on Celebrate Together
      ul
        li Engaging in vote manipulation
        li Breaking Celebrate Together or doing anything that interferes with normal use of Celebrate Together
        li Creating multiple accounts to evade punishment or avoid restrictions
      br
      | If a user of Celebrate Together does something that goes against our Content Policy, the moderators of Celebrate Together can do the following in order with the user.
      ul
        li Asking you nicely to knock it off
        li Asking you less nicely
        li Temporary or permanent suspension of accounts
        li Removal of privileges from, or adding restrictions to, accounts
        li Adding restrictions to share content
        li Removal of content
        li Banning from Celebrate Together
